    "text": "Home\nCONTACT\nGet in Touch\nAWARD\nBiletnikoff Award\nBANQUET\nAward Banquet\nSCHOLARSHIPS\nScholarships\nFOUNDATION\nThe TQC Foundation\nTQC Foundation\nFoundation Officers and Trustees\n2022-2023 TQC Foundation Committee Chairmen and Members\n2021-22 TQCF Committee Chairmen & Members\nFundraising Milestones\nNEWS\nMedia Releases\nFORUM/VOTE\nForum/Fan Vote\n2023 Biletnikoff Award Banquet\nHonoring the 2022 Biletnikoff Award Winner\nSaturday, March 4, 2023\nDunlap Champions Club at\nDoak Cambell Stadium, Tallahassee, Florida\nKeynote Speaker: Drew Pearson\nEmail BiletnikoffAward@BiletnikoffAward.com for more info\n   12345678\nListed dates include release dates for watch list, votes, semifinalists, finalists, winner announcement, and more.\nThe 2022 Biletnikoff Award Watch List\nAnnounced July 21, 2022\nSeason Receiving Statistics are compiled for the Biletnikoff Award watch list players (as they appear in the top 100 of the NCAA receiving statistics), semifinalists, and finalists (3), as appropriate.\nMedia Releases include any recent announcements or releases from the Tallahassee Quarterback Club Foundation, Inc., Biletnikoff Award.\n\nNCFAA\nThe Biletnikoff Award is a member of the National College Football Awards Association (NCFAA). The NCFAA was founded in 1997 as a coalition of the major collegiate football awards to protect, preserve and enhance the integrity, influence and prestige of the game’s predominant awards. The NCFAA encourages professionalism and the highest standards for the administration of its member awards and the selection of their candidates and recipients. For more information, visit the association’s official website, www.ncfaa.org.\nUSEFUL LINKS\nBiletnikoff Family Foundation\nCBS Sports\nCFBStats\nCollege Football AP\nCollege Football Playoff\nCollege Football Playoff Poll\nCollege Football Playoff Poll\nESPN College Football\nFootball Foundation\nFootball Outsiders\nFootball Writers Association\nNCFAA\nPro Football Focus\